Terms of Service for Community Operations Platform.

1. Introduction
These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of our Discord bot ("Bot") that is designed to inform the moderators of a server how active or inactive users on their Discord server are by applying pass and fail roles based on parameters set by the moderators.

2. Acceptance of Terms
By adding the Bot to your Discord server and using its services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use our Bot.

3. Description of Service
The Bot provides functionalities to manage and monitor user activity within a Discord server. It assigns roles to users based on their activity levels as defined by the server moderators. The Bot requires certain permissions to operate effectively, including:

Manage Roles
View Channels
View Server Insights
Send Messages
Send Messages in Threads
Manage Messages
Read Message History
Use Application Commands
Connect
Speak
Use Voice Activity

4. User Responsibilities
As a user of the Bot, you agree to:

Use the Bot in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations.
Not abuse the Bot or use it for any malicious activities.
Not modify, decompile, or reverse-engineer the Bot.

5. Moderator Responsibilities
Server moderators are responsible for:

Setting and managing the parameters for user activity.

Ensuring that the use of the Bot complies with their server's rules and guidelines.

Monitoring the roles assigned by the Bot and making necessary adjustments.

6. Data and Privacy
The Bot collects and processes data as described in our Privacy Policy. By using the Bot, you consent to the collection and use of data as outlined in the Privacy Policy.

7. Termination
We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to the Bot at our sole discretion, without prior notice or liability, for any reason whatsoever, including, without limitation, if you breach the Terms.

8. Changes to Terms
We reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to modify or replace these Terms at any time. If a revision is material, we will provide at least 30 days' notice prior to any new terms taking effect. What constitutes a material change will be determined at our sole discretion.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at communityoperationsplatform@gmail.com or contact our support team on Discord itself @ https://discord.gg/Ab2bCdCvcA.

